AND MARES, FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. $1,500 to pass the entry box and $750
additional to start, with $150,000 Guaranteed. After payment of 1% to all owners of
horses finishing sixth through last, 62% of the remaining purse shall be paid to the
owner of the winner, 20% to second, 10% to third, 5% to fourth, and 3% to fifth. Weight:
123 lbs. Non-winners of a grade I or II at nine furlongs or over on the turf since July 1
allowed 2 lbs., a graded stakes at nine furlongs or over in 2014-2015, 4lbs., $60,000 at
nine furlongs or over since September 1, 6 lbs. In the event this stakes is taken off the
turf, it may be subject to downgrading upon review of the Graded Stakes Committee.
Trophy to the winning owner. Closed Saturday, February 7, 2015 wwith 17 Nominations
and 2 Supplements. (If deemed inadvisable to run this race over the turf course, it will be
run on the main track at One Mile and One Quarter) (Rail at 12 feet)
